Triton Group Ltd said JohnStiska has resigned as its president. He will be replaced byTriton Chairman Charles Scott.    Stiska will return to private law practice and willcontinue to serve as special counsel to Triton and to IntermarkInc &lt;IMI>.    Intermark, which owns 41 pct of Triton's common stock, tooka controlling interest in the company in March, 1986. Reuter&#3;